Y \in \mathrm{R}^n
\mathrm{Cov}(X,Y)
\mathrm{Var}(X)
\mathrm{Var}(Y)
| \mathrm{Cov}(X,Y) | \le \mathrm{Var}(X)^{1/2}\mathrm{Var}(Y)^{1/2}.
\mathrm{Cov}(X,Y), \, \mathrm{Var}(X), \,\mathrm{Var}(Y) \in \mathrm{R}^{n\times n}
\mathrm{Var}(X)_{ij} = \mathrm{Cov}(X_i,X_j)
\mathrm{Cov}(X,Y) \preceq \mathrm{Var}(X)^{1/2}\left(\mathrm{Var}(Y)^{1/2}\right)'
